# Dart Coding Style Guidelines

## General
- Follow the [Effective Dart](https://dart.dev/guides/language/effective-dart) style guide
- Keep functions small and focused on a single responsibility
- Limit line length to 80 characters when possible
- Use meaningful variable and function names

## Classes and Models
- Make fields `final` when possible
- Implement proper constructors for all models
- Don't use `freezed` package or `part` syntax as specified in requirements
- Provide clear documentation for public APIs

## UI Components
- Separate business logic from UI code
- Extract reusable widgets into separate files
- Use constants for dimensions, paddings, and other UI values
- Follow Material Design guidelines for consistent UX

## Comments and Documentation
- Add meaningful comments for complex logic
- Document public APIs with dartdoc comments
- Keep comments up-to-date with code changes

## Error Handling
- Handle errors gracefully with try/catch where appropriate
- Provide meaningful error messages
- Never silently catch exceptions without proper handling

## Performance
- Minimize unnecessary rebuilds in Flutter widgets
- Use const constructors where applicable
- Be mindful of memory usage, especially with large collections